Wait, but if more than one die >4, then since we need at most one die >2, but if multiple dice are >4, they are automatically >2, so if we have more than one die >4, then we have more than one die >2, which contradicts the "at most one die >2". Therefore, the only possible case is exactly one die >4 and the rest ≤2. Therefore, the number of such outcomes is C(4,1)*2^1*2^3=4*2*8=64, as calculated earlier.
